{{Infobox government agency | name =Ministry of Education | native_name = '''وزارة التعليم'''| native_name_a = '''MoE''' | native_name_r = | type = Government body| seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | logo =MOELogo.png | logo_width = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | formed = {{Start date and age|1925}} as Directorate of Knowledge | preceding1 = Directorate of Knowledge (1925-1953) | preceding2 = Ministry of Knowledge (1953-2003)<!-- up to |preceding6= --> | dissolved = | superseding1 = | superseding2 = <!-- up to |superseding6= --> | jurisdiction = [[Government of Saudi Arabia]]| headquarters = Takhassusi St, Al Mathar Ash Shamali, [[Riyadh]] 12334, [[Saudi Arabia]] | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LATITUDE|LONGITUDE|type:landmark_region:US|display=inline,title}} --> | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = | minister1_pfo = | minister2_name = | minister2_pfo = <!-- up to |minister8_name= --> | deputyminister1_name = | deputyminister1_pfo = | deputyminister2_name = | deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- up to |deputyminister8_name= --> | chief1_name = [[Ahmed Al-Eissa|Dr. Ahmed bin Mohammad Al-Issa]]| chief1_position = Minister of Education| chief2_name = | chief2_position = <!-- up to |chief9_name= --> | public_protector = | deputy = | parent_department = | parent_agency = | child1_agency = | child2_agency = <!-- up to |child25_agency= --> | keydocument1 = <!-- up to |keydocument6= --> | website = [http://www.moe.gov.sa/en/ www.moe.gov.sa] | agency_id = | map = | map_size = | map_caption = | footnotes = | embed = }} The '''Ministry of Education''' ('''MOE'''; {{lang-ar|وزارة التعليم}}) is a ministry of [[Saudi Arabia]]. As of December 2015, Dr. [[Ahmed bin Mohammad Al-Issa]] is the minister.<ref>"[http://he.moe.gov.sa/en/Ministry/Excellency-Of-The-Ministe/Pages/default.aspx The Minister] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150628073605/http://he.moe.gov.sa/en/Ministry/Excellency-Of-The-Ministe/Pages/default.aspx |date=2015-06-28 }}." Ministry of Education of Saudi Arabia, Higher Education. retrieved on November 5, 2015.</ref> Headquartered in [[Riyadh]],<ref>"[https://www.saudiembassy.net/about/ministry_addresses_in_saudi_arabia.aspx Ministry Addresses] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924094606/http://www.saudiembassy.net/about/ministry_addresses_in_saudi_arabia.aspx |date=2015-09-24 }}." Royal Embassy of Saudi Arabia Washington, DC. Retrieved on November 5, 2015. "Ministry of Education Airport Road, Riyadh 11148 "</ref> it oversees primary, secondary, and higher education.
==History== In 1926, [[Ibn Saud|Sultan of Nejd Abdul Aziz Ibn Saud]] annexed [[Kingdom of Hejaz]] and dissolved the government of [[Hijaz]] as well as the [[Sultanate of Nejd]] and established the [[Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz]] with running a dual monarchy. [[Ibn Saud|King Abdul Aziz Al-Saud]] established the Council for Knowledge which focused on education in [[Hejaz]] region. In 1953, [[Saud of Saudi Arabia|King Saud bin Abdul Aziz Al-Saud]] established and merged the previous Directorate of Knowledge to Ministry of Knowledge and appointed the then [[Fahd of Saudi Arabia|Prince Fahd bin Abdul Aziz Al-Saud]] as the Minister on December 24, 1953. In 1960, [[Faisal of Saudi Arabia|Crown Prince Faisal bin Abdul Aziz Al-Saud]] established General Presidency for Girls’ Education. In 2002, [[Fahd of Saudi Arabia|King Fahd bin Abdul Aziz Al-Saud]] issued a royal decree which merged General Presidency for Girls’ Education to the Ministry of Knowledge and the Ministry was renamed as Ministry of Education in 2003. ==Achievements== In September 2018, Ministry of Education and the [[Arizona State University]] partnered with each other in order to launch Building Leadership for Change Through School Immersion program which would commence from February 2019.
